name: Ankita Classic Warkhand Road

reviews.review_text: The prawns in the starters were enjoyable, but unfortunately, the mix fried rice contained artificial prawns instead of real ones, which was disappointing. The overall experience was below average as the hospitality was not up to the mark. While some dishes were decent, the food quality overall left room for improvement.

A Must-Visit Gem on Warkhand Road – Ankita Classic!

While traveling from Goa towards Maharashtra, we stumbled upon Ankita Classic on Warkhand Road, and it turned out to be the highlight of our journey! From the moment we stepped in, it was a delightful experience, thanks to the warm hospitality of Host Rahul Dalvi, who made us feel right at home.

The seafood is nothing short of awesome – fresh, flavorful, and perfectly cooked! The portions were generous, and the pricing was unbelievably reasonable for the quality and quantity we received.

The interiors are simply outstanding – a visual treat! It’s rare to find such a beautifully designed space along the highway. With a seating capacity of over 350 people, it’s perfect for large gatherings, yet cozy enough for a family meal.

Parking is often a challenge on long road trips, but not here – there’s ample parking space to accommodate vehicles of all sizes.

If you’re a seafood lover and appreciate great ambiance, Ankita Classic is a must-visit. It’s more than just a restaurant; it’s an experience you’ll cherish! Don’t miss this gem if you’re traveling in the area.

I visited this place twice and it was fantastic. Large parking space, good ambience, staffs behaviour was good all are cooperative. I tasted 10 different types of fishes here and all were good in taste. Actually I ordered starters those were good in taste and later ordered thali. Thali was good but not able to finish full thali because it was too big. So I would suggest if you order starters then surely go for small thali and share big thali because lots of food will waste later. So, I would suggest you should visit this place once if you are seafood lover and it is affordable not too costly.

description:
Nestled within the vibrant Corlim Industrial Estate, **Ankita Classic** on Warkhand Road boasts an impressive rating of **4.5 stars** from **3,650 reviews**, solidifying its reputation as a beloved spot among seafood aficionados. This gem has emerged as a go-to destination for those seeking mouth-watering **seafood**, famed for its **fish thali**, and an array of delicacies that include **kingfish** and **squids**.

### Ambiance & Design
Upon entering, guests are greeted by an inviting and beautifully designed interior that enhances the dining experience. The space, with a capacity for over **350 diners**, strikes a delicate balance between accommodating large groups and maintaining a cozy atmosphere for family meals. The photographs shared by patrons reveal a meticulous attention to detail in décor, blending local aesthetic with modern touches. Soft lighting creates a warm ambiance, complemented by tasteful art pieces that adorn the walls. Some reviews noted a pleasantly upbeat background tune that sets a lively yet comfortable dining vibe.

### Menu & Culinary Experience
The culinary offerings at Ankita Classic are indeed a highlight. The menu showcases an impressive variety of **seafood delicacies** that have received considerable praise. Signature dishes include the **fish thali**, known for its portion size and authentic flavors, making it a popular choice among diners. Reviewers have raved about the **freshness and flavor** of the seafood, with many excited to taste multiple types of fish, often ordering **starters** followed by generous thalis. The photographs provided by customers illustrate beautifully presented dishes, capturing the vibrant colors and textures of an assortment of seafood that would tantalize any palate. While some patrons expressed disappointment with certain dishes, particularly noting a mix of artificial elements in the fried rice, others affirmed the overall quality and satisfaction derived from their seafood choices. 

### Customer Experience & Service
The service at Ankita Classic has received mixed reviews, with a notable mention of the warm hospitality from the host, **Rahul Dalvi**, who makes guests feel welcomed. While some reviews highlighted issues with promptness and attentiveness, others found the staff to be friendly and cooperative, adding to the overall positive dining experience. The restaurant provides ample parking—a crucial convenience for road-trippers—and many found it easy to navigate their dining experience. Reservations or walk-ins seem manageable, although, given its popularity, arriving early is advisable during peak times.

### Popularity & Reviews
Ankita Classic has carved out a significant presence on social media and among food bloggers, with many describing it as a **"must-visit"** while traveling through the area. The consistent flip of praise, particularly for its seafood offerings, showcases a commendable effort in maintaining quality. Additionally, this restaurant seems to have captured the interest of local food critics, further solidifying its status as a point of interest along Warkhand Road.

### Utilizing Visual Content
Customer-uploaded photographs lend authenticity to the dining experience at Ankita Classic. Images reveal the vibrant presentation of dishes that entice patrons from the moment they arrive. The inviting ambiance, paired with the stunning visual arrays of seafood platters, underscores the restaurant's commitment to creating a memorable dining experience.

In conclusion, **Ankita Classic** stands out as a beloved seafood restaurant that harmonizes good food with a delightful dining environment. Whether you're passing through or seeking a designated dining trip, this place promises not just a meal, but an experience worth savoring. With its robust reputation and consistent customer appreciation, a visit here is bound to enrich your culinary journey.
